criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  classification of gross motor function with levels I and II according to the Gross
             Motor Function Classification System (GMFCS),

          -  MACS (Manual Ability Classification System) classification between levels I and II.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  over 20 years;

          -  comorbidities that prevent the accomplishment of the activity;

          -  people with significant visual and cognitive impairment;

          -  those who have undergone chemical blockade or upper limb surgery for less than six
             months
